Netlify provides an official Model Context Protocol (MCP) server that enables AI agents to interact with the Netlify platform to build, deploy, and manage projects via natural language [1][2].

You can connect to this server using supported clients like Cursor, Windsurf, or Claude Desktop [1][3]. For a local setup, add this configuration to your MCP settings file [1][3]:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "netlify": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@netlify/mcp"]
    }
  }
}
```

Alternatively, you can connect to the remote instance at `https://netlify-mcp.netlify.app/mcp` using the appropriate HTTP transport configuration for your specific AI tool [4]. The server exposes tools, resources, and prompts, allowing agents to handle tasks like managing environment variables, configuring extensions, and accessing deploy logs [1][2].
